				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charmed pets (not Dire-Charm) scale linearly. If the charmed pet does MOB_HP-1 damage, it eats 30% exp. If it does 0 damage, it eats 0% exp.
<br />
So if a charmed pet does 50% of the damage, it eats 15% exp.
<br />

<br />
In PoP at least, I encourage Enchanters and Druids to use a Dire Charm pet. It's highly unlikely a level 46 mob that does ~ 120 damage per hit will do more than 50% damage over a full group.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
